        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Correct Answer in Next Question",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "2601 CMDT learners, 513 CBDT learners and 10000 Junyi learners",
          "Maths & Biology",
          "Questions and Answers, Pre-requisite Concept Mapping",
          "[Question Text, Question Image, Prerequisite Relation Graph]",
          "Multiple Item Response Theory models foten do not consider cross-modal information about similar exercises (difficulty and contents). \n\nModels do not consider cognitive complexity of concepts.",
          "The model includes a set of modules capabble of handling contextual information from different formats (image and/or text). It looks to create multiple embeddings from these differrent sources AND then computes similarity via an affinity matrix.\n\n\n",
          "The model includes 3 distinct modules:\n\nThe first module is about the extraction of features from the multi-modal data (CA-GCF) - where we create embeddings from BERT (on text) and ResNet (on images). These are fused together. \n\nSubsequently, the authors also have a pre-requisite mappuiuung of concepts and create an embedding of knowledge concepts.\n\nExercises and Learners are One-Hot Encoded. ",
          "IRT, MIRT, PMF, NeuralCD, RCD, CMNCD",
          "Holdout Method",
          "CBDT\n{Accuracy: 0.7902 - CMNCD, AUC: 0.8438 - CMNCD, RMSE: 39.45 - CMNCD}\n\nCMDT\n{Accuracy: 0.7689 - CMNCD, AUC: 0.8408 - CMNCD, RMSE: 39.51 - CMNCD}\n\nCBDT\n{Accuracy: 0.7804 - CMNCD, AUC: 0.8382 - CMNCD, RMSE: 40.12 - CMNCD}\n",
          "Author proposes a new model specific for multi-modal exercises. The authors make a comparison between different model and see that CMNCD outperforms all others.\n\nThe ablation study shows that all elements of the arquitecture (text, Image, CA-GCF, Concept Complexity, Deep MIRT and Exercise contents) are relevant as the best performance is only achieved when all modules are includes.",
          "- Specific for cross-modal exercises (text and images).\n\n- Does not seem to consider many of the most well-established KT models.\n\n- Assumes Pre-Requisite Knowledge Graph is “fixed”.\n\n- Holdout Method\n\n- Dynamic learning of exercises’ trait based on concept complexity. It is currently done offline. "
        ]
      ],
      "index": 8
    }
