    {
      "id": "26a7d3fb-a939-414d-a422-0f4532003659",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "However, the current ways to model exercise traits struggle with cross-modal exercises. To mitifgate this gap, the authors propose a Deep Cross-Modal Neural Cognitive Diagnosis Framework that first, builds on current models but also exlores cross-modal contents of exercises for better modelling of student performance. The model also seems to be effective at understanding pre-requisite relationships between concepts. ",
